title: Zhil'naya Mountain
text: Zhil'naya Mountain () is the central <a href="mountain">mountain</a>, 2,560 m, of the <a href="Svarthausane%20Crags">Svarthausane Crags</a>, in <a href="S%C3%BCdliche%20Petermann%20Range">Südliche Petermann Range</a>, <a href="Wohlthat%20Mountains">Wohlthat Mountains</a>, <a href="Queen%20Maud%20Land">Queen Maud Land</a>. Discovered and plotted from air photos by <a href="Third%20German%20Antarctic%20Expedition">German Antarctic Expedition</a>, 1938–39. Mapped from air photos and surveys by <a href="Sixth%20Norwegian%20Antarctic%20Expedition">Norwegian Antarctic Expedition</a>, 1956–60; remapped by <a href="Soviet%20Antarctic%20Expedition">Soviet Antarctic Expedition</a>, 1960–61, and named "Gora Zhil'naya" (branching mountain).
